        "description": {
            "name": "description",
            "type": "java.lang.String",
            "value": "In my app, i have two modules :\r\n\r\nModOne and ModTwo. Each modules have directory 'view' in module directory with scripts.\r\nIn each module, i have one controller IndexController with an action index.\r\n\r\nIn Mod1 config :\r\n{code:xml}\r\n'Zend\\View\\Resolver\\TemplatePathStack' => array(\r\n                'parameters' => array(\r\n                    'paths'  => array(\r\n                        'mod1' => __DIR__ . '\/..\/view',\r\n                    ),\r\n                ),\r\n            ),\r\n{code}\r\nIn Mod2 config :\r\n{code:xml}\r\n'Zend\\View\\Resolver\\TemplatePathStack' => array(\r\n                'parameters' => array(\r\n                    'paths'  => array(\r\n                        'mod2' => __DIR__ . '\/..\/view',\r\n                    ),\r\n                ),\r\n            ),\r\n{code}\r\nFirst literal route \"\/mod1\" route to Mod1 index\/index.\r\nSecond literal route \"\/mod2\" route to Mod2 index\/index.\r\n\r\nBut, with the zf2, the Zend\\View\\Resolver\\TemplatePathStack, the resolve method get the first which matched. But, two paths are good : Mod1\/view and Mod2\/view.\r\n\r\nSo route \"www.exemple.com\/mod1\" route to Mod1 controller and display Mod1\/index\/index.\r\nSo route \"www.exemple.com\/mod1\" route to Mod1 controller BUT display Mod1\/index\/index, not Mod2\/index\/index.\r\n\r\nI know why, because Zend\\View\\Resolver\\TemplatePathStack :\r\n\r\n{code:xml}\r\npublic function resolve($name, Renderer $renderer = null)\r\n{\r\n        [...]\r\n\r\n        foreach ($this->paths as $path) {\r\n            $file = new SplFileInfo($path . $name);\r\n{code}\r\n\r\nThe two paths are valid, because there is \"index\" directory in each modules, and an \"index\" script in each modules.\r\n\r\nAlias, namespaced controlle name or setPaths() of Zend\\View\\Resolver\\TemplatePathStack can resolve problem, but why can we add this native comportement ? ZF1 to ZF2 migration can be hard because developer use lot of IndexController name ?"
        },
